---json
{
  "layout": "layouts/t-location.njk",
  "permalink": "/find-an-accountant/new-york/cities/manhattan/",
  "slug": "ny-manhattan",
  "tierClass": "section--tier-hub",
  "bodyClass": "page--location",
  "callBar": true,
  "title": "Manhattan QuickBooks Bookkeeping &middot; Sales Tax, UBT &amp; Commercial Rent Tax &middot; TechBrot",
  "description": "Bookkeeping for Manhattan businesses by a Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor — 8.875% sales tax, the 4% UBT, and the Commercial Rent Tax (the one borough where CRT applies) tracked and CPA-ready. Fixed-fee, remote.",
  "breadcrumb": [
    { "name": "Home", "href": "/" },
    { "name": "Find an Accountant", "href": "/find-an-accountant/" },
    { "name": "New York", "href": "/find-an-accountant/new-york/" },
    { "name": "Cities", "href": "/find-an-accountant/new-york/cities/" },
    { "name": "New York City", "href": "/find-an-accountant/new-york/cities/new-york-city/" },
    { "name": "Manhattan" }
  ],
  "heroFigure": "taccount",
  "hero": {
    "trust": [
      "Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor team",
      "Independent &middot; not Intuit",
      "Fixed-fee &middot; written scope in 3 days"
    ],
    "eyebrow": "Manhattan &middot; New York City &middot; New York County",
    "heading": "Manhattan bookkeeping &mdash; the only borough with three NYC taxes to track.",
    "subheading": "Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor bookkeeping for Manhattan businesses &mdash; the 8.875% sales tax, the 4% Unincorporated Business Tax, and the Commercial Rent Tax that applies <em>only</em> in Manhattan south of 96th Street. Reconciled, CPA-ready, and handled by a named bookkeeper on the same file every month.",
    "actions": [
      { "label": "Book the discovery call", "href": "/contact/?intent=new-york&state=new-york&city=manhattan&source_type=city-page&funnel_stage=MOFU", "class": "btn--primary" },
      { "label": "Get the free file review", "href": "/quickbooks/file-review/?intent=file-review", "class": "btn--ghost" },
      { "label": "Speak to a ProAdvisor", "tel": true, "class": "btn--ghost" }
    ]
  },
  "inBrief": {
    "text": "<strong>TechBrot</strong> delivers <strong>Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor bookkeeping for Manhattan businesses</strong> &mdash; monthly bookkeeping, <a href=\"/find-an-accountant/new-york/quickbooks-cleanup/\">cleanup</a>, and QuickBooks management by a named bookkeeper on the same file every month. The full Manhattan summary is below.",
    "source": "Reviewed by the Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor team at TechBrot Inc., an independent firm &mdash; not affiliated with Intuit Inc. Manhattan (New York County) tax figures verified against the NYC Department of Finance and NY DTF."
  },
  "ctaBand": {
    "eyebrow": "Manhattan businesses start here",
    "heading": "Ready for a Manhattan bookkeeper who knows all three NYC taxes?",
    "lede": "Book a free discovery call. We&rsquo;ll review your QuickBooks file and your Manhattan situation &mdash; sales tax, UBT, and any CRT exposure &mdash; and send a written fixed-fee quote within 3 business days. No pitch. Independent firm &mdash; does not file NY/NYC taxes; coordinates with your CPA.",
    "actions": [
      { "label": "Book the discovery call", "href": "/contact/?intent=new-york&state=new-york&city=manhattan&source_type=city-page&funnel_stage=BOFU", "class": "btn--primary" },
      { "label": "Speak to a ProAdvisor", "tel": true, "class": "btn--ghost" }
    ]
  }
}
---

{# ── SUMMARY · real H2 carrying the Manhattan summary prose (right after the in-brief). (H2: The short version.) ── #}
<section class="section section--compact" id="ny-manhattan-summary">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <h2 class="section__heading">The short version.</h2>
    </header>
    <p class="prose">{{ summarized | safe }}</p>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── AI SUMMARY · five-question block. (H2: Manhattan bookkeeping, in five questions.) ── #}
<section class="section" id="ny-manhattan-ai-summary">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">For AI engines &amp; quick answers</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Manhattan bookkeeping, in five questions.</h2>
    </header>
    <dl class="ai-summary ai-summary--ruled" id="ny-manhattan-ai-summary-list">
      {%- for item in aiSummary %}
      <div class="ai-summary__item">
        <dt class="ai-summary__question">{{ item.q | safe }}</dt>
        <dd class="ai-summary__answer"><p>{{ item.a | safe }}</p></dd>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </dl>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── LOCAL CONTEXT · the un-clonable band (the real-Manhattan CRT-anchored prose). (H2: Why Manhattan books carry an extra layer.) ── #}
<section class="section section--alt" id="ny-manhattan-local">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Bookkeeping built for how Manhattan actually operates</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Why Manhattan books carry an extra layer.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="stack-8">
      {%- for p in localContext %}<p class="prose">{{ p | safe }}</p>{%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── AREAS · across the borough; each area a real H3. (H2: Manhattan businesses we keep clean. + 6 H3s) ── #}
<section class="section" id="ny-manhattan-areas">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Across the borough</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Manhattan businesses we keep clean.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="grid-3">
      {%- for a in areas %}
      <div class="stack-8">
        <h3>{{ a.name | safe }}</h3>
        <p class="prose">{{ a.note | safe }}</p>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── TAX STACK · plain grid-3 + stack-8 (NOT proof-strip — overflow rule). (H2: Manhattan's tax stack — three layers, not two.) ── #}
<section class="section section--alt" id="ny-manhattan-tax">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">The Manhattan tax picture we build into your books</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Manhattan&rsquo;s tax stack &mdash; three layers, not two.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="grid-3">
      {%- for t in taxStack %}
      <div class="stack-8">
        <p class="stat__value">{{ t.figure | safe }}</p>
        <p class="prose">{{ t.desc | safe }}</p>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
    <p class="prose"><small>{{ taxNote | safe }}</small></p>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── CRT EXPLAINER · bespoke Manhattan section; each step a real H3. (H2: The Commercial Rent Tax, explained. + 4 H3s) ── #}
<section class="section" id="ny-manhattan-crt">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">The tax unique to Manhattan</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">The Commercial Rent Tax, explained.</h2>
      <p class="section__lede">{{ crtLede | safe }}</p>
    </header>
    <div class="stack-8">
      {%- for c in crt %}
      <div class="stack-8">
        <h3>{{ c.title | safe }}</h3>
        <p class="prose">{{ c.body | safe }}</p>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
    <p class="prose"><small>{{ crtNote | safe }}</small></p>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── INDUSTRIES · Manhattan verticals (lighter chips-list into NY industry pages). (H2: Built for Manhattan's core sectors.) ── #}
<section class="section section--alt" id="ny-manhattan-industries">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Manhattan verticals we know</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Built for Manhattan&rsquo;s core sectors.</h2>
      <p class="section__lede">Each links to our dedicated New York industry page, with the local wrinkles built in.</p>
    </header>
    <ul class="checks-list">
      {%- for i in industries %}
      <li><a href="{{ i.href }}">{{ i.label | safe }}</a> &mdash; {{ i.note | safe }}</li>
      {%- endfor %}
    </ul>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── SERVICES · value stack (grid-2 buyer-cards). (H2: Everything your Manhattan books need, one expert. + 4 H3s) ── #}
<section class="section" id="ny-manhattan-services">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">What a named ProAdvisor does for your Manhattan books</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Everything your Manhattan books need, one expert.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="grid-2">
      {%- for s in services %}
      <article class="buyer-card">
        <p class="buyer-card__opener">{{ s.num }}</p>
        <h3 class="buyer-card__heading">{{ s.title | safe }}</h3>
        <p class="buyer-card__body">{{ s.body | safe }}</p>
        <a class="buyer-card__cta" href="{{ s.href }}">{{ s.cta | safe }}</a>
      </article>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── ADVISORY · standing brand line. (H2: Automation handles the data entry. We handle the judgment.) ── #}
<section class="section section--alt" id="ny-manhattan-advisory">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">The advisory line</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Automation handles the data entry. We handle the judgment.</h2>
    </header>
    <p class="prose">{{ advisoryBody | safe }}</p>
    <div class="hero__actions">
      <a class="btn btn--primary btn--lg" href="/contact/?intent=new-york&amp;state=new-york&amp;city=manhattan&amp;source_type=city-page&amp;funnel_stage=BOFU">Book the discovery call</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── FAQ · 8 verbatim Q/A; visible faq__list = FAQPage schema (same array). (H2: Manhattan bookkeeping questions.) ── #}
<section class="section" id="ny-manhattan-faq">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Common questions</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Manhattan bookkeeping questions.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="faq__list">
      {%- for item in faq %}
      <div class="faq__item">
        <h3 class="faq__question">
          <button class="faq__trigger" type="button" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="ny-manhattan-faq-a{{ loop.index }}">{{ item.q | safe }}</button>
        </h3>
        <div class="faq__answer" id="ny-manhattan-faq-a{{ loop.index }}" data-open="false">
          <p>{{ item.a | safe }}</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── EXPERT REVIEW · firm-level, no founder name (byline-block + meta-reviewed). (H2: Reviewed by the TechBrot Certified ProAdvisor team.) ── #}
<section class="section section--alt" id="ny-manhattan-review">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Page review &amp; standards</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Reviewed by the TechBrot Certified ProAdvisor team.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="byline-block">
      <div class="byline-block__mark" aria-hidden="true"></div>
      <div>
        <p class="byline-block__name">By the Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor team</p>
        <p class="byline-block__review">TechBrot Inc. &middot; Independent Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor firm</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="prose">
      <p>Reviewed and maintained by the accounting team at <strong>TechBrot Inc.</strong>, an independent Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor firm serving Manhattan and the wider New York City market. Manhattan tax figures &mdash; 8.875% combined sales tax; 4% UBT after the $95,000 gross-income threshold, with a credit fully offsetting UBT of $3,400 or less; and the Commercial Rent Tax, effective ~3.9% on base rent at $250,000+ annualized, with a full small-business credit under $5M income and $500K rent, applicable only in Manhattan south of 96th Street &mdash; reflect <a href="https://www.nyc.gov/site/finance/index.page" rel="noopener nofollow">NYC Department of Finance</a> and <a href="https://www.tax.ny.gov/" rel="noopener nofollow">NY DTF</a> rules current as of the date below and are reviewed periodically. TechBrot provides bookkeeping and coordinates with your CPA, who files.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="trust-row">
      {%- for c in reviewCreds %}
      <div class="trust-row__item"><p class="trust-row__value">{{ c.label }}</p><p class="trust-row__label">{{ c.detail | safe }}</p></div>
      {%- if not loop.last %}<div class="trust-row__divider"></div>{%- endif %}
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
    <p class="meta-reviewed"><span>Published: 2026-06-15</span><span>Updated: 2026-06-15</span><span>Reviewed: 2026-06-15 &middot; Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor</span></p>
  </div>
</section>
